<h1>Section 4 — Target JIRA &amp; ServiceNow Integrations</h1>
<p>How Copado (owned and configured by the DevX Automation Team) resolves every current gap in JIRA and ServiceNow integration.</p>

<table>
  <colgroup>
    <col style="width: 50%;" />
    <col style="width: 50%;" />
  </colgroup>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <th><strong>Current Problem</strong></th>
      <th><strong>Copado Target Solution</strong></th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>
        <p><strong>JIRA · Gap 1 — No enforced PR → JIRA story link</strong></p>
        <p>Commit messages and branch names reference JIRA IDs by team convention only. No tooling enforces the link, validates the ID, or auto-attaches the commit to a user story. Traceability depends entirely on developer discipline.</p>
        <ac:structured-macro ac:name="status"><ac:parameter ac:name="colour">Red</ac:parameter><ac:parameter ac:name="title">Manual Convention</ac:parameter></ac:structured-macro>
      </td>
      <td>
        <p><strong>JIRA · Solution 1 — Bidirectional User Story sync</strong></p>
        <p>JIRA stories sync to Copado User Story objects via native integration configured by DevX. PRs and commits are automatically associated to the relevant story. The link is enforced by the platform — not convention.</p>
        <ac:structured-macro ac:name="status"><ac:parameter ac:name="colour">Green</ac:parameter><ac:parameter ac:name="title">◆ Copado Native Sync</ac:parameter></ac:structured-macro>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>
        <p><strong>JIRA · Gap 2 — No auto status update on deployment</strong></p>
        <p>After a story is deployed to production, the JIRA ticket must be manually updated. No pipeline event triggers a status change — leading to stale story states and inaccurate sprint reporting.</p>
        <ac:structured-macro ac:name="status"><ac:parameter ac:name="colour">Red</ac:parameter><ac:parameter ac:name="title">Manual Update</ac:parameter></ac:structured-macro>
      </td>
      <td>
        <p><strong>JIRA · Solution 2 — Deploy triggers automatic status update</strong></p>
        <p>When a Copado User Story is promoted to Production, the linked JIRA ticket is automatically moved to Done. No developer action required — sprint reporting is always accurate.</p>
        <ac:structured-macro ac:name="status"><ac:parameter ac:name="colour">Green</ac:parameter><ac:parameter ac:name="title">◆ Event-Driven Automation</ac:parameter></ac:structured-macro>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>
        <p><strong>SNOW · Gap 1 — CR approval is not a hard pipeline gate</strong></p>
        <p>The pipeline auto-creates the SNOW CR, but does not enforce that approval must be granted before deployment. This relies on the team manually coordinating — which breaks down under time pressure.</p>
        <ac:structured-macro ac:name="status"><ac:parameter ac:name="colour">Yellow</ac:parameter><ac:parameter ac:name="title">Missing Gate</ac:parameter></ac:structured-macro>
      </td>
      <td>
        <p><strong>SNOW · Solution 1 — CR approval unblocks the pipeline</strong></p>
        <p>Copado's native ServiceNow integration polls the CR status. The deployment pipeline is blocked until the CR reaches Approved in SNOW. No manual coordination needed — the system enforces the gate automatically.</p>
        <ac:structured-macro ac:name="status"><ac:parameter ac:name="colour">Green</ac:parameter><ac:parameter ac:name="title">◆ Hard Pipeline Gate</ac:parameter></ac:structured-macro>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>
        <p><strong>SNOW · Gap 2 — Manual CR close after deployment</strong></p>
        <p>After a successful production deployment, the release manager must manually return to ServiceNow and move the Change Request through Review to Closed. No automation, no deadline enforcement.</p>
        <ac:structured-macro ac:name="status"><ac:parameter ac:name="colour">Red</ac:parameter><ac:parameter ac:name="title">Manual Closure</ac:parameter></ac:structured-macro>
      </td>
      <td>
        <p><strong>SNOW · Solution 2 — Copado auto-closes the CR on success</strong></p>
        <p>When Copado registers a successful production deployment, it automatically updates the SNOW CR to Closed via the native integration. The full CR lifecycle — create, gate, close — is managed by Copado without manual intervention.</p>
        <ac:structured-macro ac:name="status"><ac:parameter ac:name="colour">Green</ac:parameter><ac:parameter ac:name="title">◆ Full Lifecycle Automation</ac:parameter></ac:structured-macro>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

